    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-12T18:12:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-12T18:12:00-05:00" n="525"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.115St2/114</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-12T18:12:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1915, 6.12 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1408. Your April 8, 1907. You will say to British Government, in replying to its
                    statement regarding release steamer <hi rend="italic">Wico</hi>, that this
                    Government considers that any seizure of American cargoes which might be made by
                    the German authorities would be a matter which should be adjusted between the
                    Government of the United States and the German Government, and further say that
                    the Government of the United States does not perceive that any such action on
                    the part of the German authorities could afford justification for seizures of
                    American cargoes by the British authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
